I"7<p>If logging into an SSH server takes a long time, this configuration modifications might help:</p>

<ol>
  <li>In <code class="highlighter-rouge">/etc/ssh/sshd_config</code> make sure those lines are set or uncommented:
    <div class="highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>GSSAPIAuthentication no
GSSAPIDelegateCredentials yes
UseDNS no
</code></pre></div>    </div>
  </li>
  <li>In <code class="highlighter-rouge">/etc/nsswitch.conf</code> set the values like this:
    <div class="highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>passwd:         compat
group:          compat
shadow:         compat
</code></pre></div>    </div>
  </li>
</ol>

